{
  "texts": [
    "We did not edit the vignettes in any other way, because the principles of representative design require stimuli to be as close to the actual decision environment as possible.",
    "Any modification could unpredictably affect the cues and their correlations to self-triage decisions and thus the representativeness of the vignettes.",
    "Using this sampling method, the RepVig Framework, we compiled a final set of 45 vignettes to construct a set that is comparable in size to previous studies 10, 14.",
    "In alignment with established best practices and previous SAA research 14, 16, 38, two licensed physicians assessed the appropriate triage level (i.e., if the symptoms require emergency care, non-emergency care, or selfcare) of each vignette independently.",
    "After rating all vignettes, the physicians discussed their answers in cases of disagreement to reach consensus on the appropriate triage level, thereby finalizing the solutions for this set."
  ]
}